";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:37:\"5879777@http://wordpress.org/support/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:500:\"<p>first of all, it sounds like your first problem is that there might be a conflict with another plugin - start by deactivating other plugins that might interfere to see if that\'s the problem</p>\n<p>The caching plugin is what is responsible for posts not showing up immediately on your site - that is what caching software does.  If you want to see the most current posts, you need to delete the cache.\n</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~4/Cdq9zc6-5V4\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:86:\"http://wordpress.org/support/topic/rss-multi-importer-with-w3-total-cache#post-5879777\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:62:\"altatt on &quot;W3 Total Cache affects another subdomain&quot;\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:99:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~3/wHyIkuUt0FQ/w3-total-cache-affects-another-subdomain\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Sun, 10 Aug 2014 04:06:19 PDT\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:37:\"5879359@http://wordpress.org/support/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1008:\"<p>Hi,</p>\n<p>W3 Total Cache is a great plugin. I have WordPress installation on my home directory. I\'ve installed the plugin and everything seems to work well on the site. The problem is that I have a Prestashop installation on my home directory too, accessed using a subdomain, and when I activate W3 Total Cache plugin, Prestashop\'s back-office pages aren\'t refreshed. Is there any solution?</p>\n<p>Here I detail an example of the structure:</p>\n<pre><code>/web-folder\n     .htaccess (generated by W3 Total Cache)\n     /site (wordpress installation)\n     /shop (prestashop installation)</code></pre>\n<p><a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.mydomain.com\">http://www.mydomain.com</a> -&#62; wordpress site<br />\nshop.mydomain.com -&#62; prestashop site</p>\n<p><a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/w3-total-cache/\">https://wordpress.org/plugins/w3-total-cache/</a>\n</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~4/wHyIkuUt0FQ\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"http://wordpress.org/support/topic/w3-total-cache-affects-another-subdomain#post-5879359\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";